{
  "texts": [
    "BioBERT, the BERT model optimized for biomedical text mining, is domain-specific, and is pre-trained on PubMed abstracts and PMC articles [19].",
    "BioBERT can easily be fine-tuned to perform text extraction tasks, and has been successfully applied to tasks such as the allocation of phenotypes to protein-protein interactions and the extraction of drug-drug interactions [35, 36].",
    "It has outperformed other state-ofthe-art NLP-based RE methods in the biological domain [19].",
    "Named entity recognition (NER) and biological NER (BioNER), identifies biological entities such as genes, proteins, diseases, drugs, and miRNAs [37].",
    "BioNER methods fall into one of three categories: (1) knowledge-based; (2) rule-based; or (3) machine learning [38]."
  ]
}